* Operations::
@end menu

@node Diffing
@subsection Diffing

@enumerate
@item
@anchor{Diff Transient}Diff Transient


@table @asis
@item @kbd{d} (@code{majutsu-diff})
@kindex d
@findex majutsu-diff
Open the Diff transient.
@end table

Useful transient entries include:
@table @asis
@item @kbd{r}
@kindex r
Select revisions to diff (@samp{--revisions}). Can specify multiple revisions or a revset like @samp{B::D}.
@item @kbd{f / t}
@kindex f / t
Select the @samp{--from} and @samp{--to} revisions.
@item @kbd{--}
@kindex --
Limit diff to selected files/filesets.
@item @kbd{-g}
@kindex -g
Toggle Git-style diff output.
@item @kbd{-W}
@kindex -W
Toggle color-words diff output.
@item @kbd{-S}
@kindex -S
Toggle stat output.
@item @kbd{-s}
@kindex -s
Toggle summary output.
@item @kbd{-c}
@kindex -c
Set context line count.
@item @kbd{-b / -w}
@kindex -b / -w
Ignore whitespace amount / ignore all whitespace.
@item @kbd{W}
@kindex W
Save the current diff arguments as defaults for this jj repository.
@end table

@item
@anchor{Understanding @samp{--revisions}}Understanding @samp{--revisions}


The @samp{--revisions} argument accepts any revset that forms a @emph{contiguous} set of commits. "Contiguous" means no gaps in the DAG@comma{} but @strong{forks and merges are allowed}.

Examples:
@table @asis
@item @samp{-r @@}
Changes in the working copy commit (default).
@item @samp{-r @@-}
Changes in the parent of the working copy.
@item @samp{-r B::D}
Total changes from B through D@.
@item @samp{-r 'A | B'}
Valid only if A and B form a contiguous set; gaps produce an error.
@end table

When visiting a file from such a diff@comma{} Majutsu uses the exact range stored by
the diff buffer:
@itemize
@item
On an @strong{added} or @strong{context} line: resolve the @samp{--revisions} expression itself.
@item
On a @strong{removed} line: resolve the parents of that expression
(@samp{REVSET-} in revset syntax).
@end itemize

Blob buffers require that the chosen side resolve to exactly one revision.
Majutsu reports an error rather than arbitrarily choosing one head or root.

@strong{Note}: When the revset has multiple heads or roots@comma{} the target revision for file visits may be ambiguous. For example@comma{} in an X-shaped history:
@example
D   E       <- two heads
 \ /
  C
 / \
A   B       <- two roots
@end example
If you diff @samp{-r A::D | B::E}@comma{} there are two heads (D@comma{} E) and two roots (A@comma{} B). The diff shows changes from the @emph{merged} parents to the @emph{merged} heads. If D and E modify the same lines@comma{} the diff can show conflict markers. Inspection of the combined diff still works@comma{} but visiting a blob from either ambiguous side fails the single-revision check. Use @samp{--from} / @samp{--to} with single revisions when precise file navigation matters.

@item
@anchor{Diff Buffer (1)}Diff Buffer


The diff buffer is highly interactive:

For a diff of exactly one change@comma{} Majutsu displays collapsible revision
headers and the change description above the diff.  This includes the default
working-copy diff and an explicit @samp{-r} or @samp{--revisions} revset that resolves to
one change.  The metadata is omitted for @samp{--from} / @samp{--to} ranges and revsets
that resolve to zero or multiple changes.  Bookmark labels use structured jj
template fields available in every supported jj version@comma{} so remote-only
bookmarks and names containing spaces@comma{} sigils@comma{} or @samp{@@} are preserved.  Control
characters are escaped when rendered to keep the collapsible heading on one line.

@table @asis
@item @kbd{@key{RET}} (@code{majutsu-diff-visit-file})
@kindex RET
@findex majutsu-diff-visit-file
Visit the appropriate version of the file at point. For working copy diffs@comma{} added/context lines visit the workspace file while removed lines visit the parent-side blob. For committed changes@comma{} it visits the blob at the corresponding side.
@item @kbd{C-j / C-<return> (Vanilla)} (@code{majutsu-diff-visit-workspace-file})
@kindex C-j / C-<return> (Vanilla)
@findex majutsu-diff-visit-workspace-file
Visit the workspace file@comma{} regardless of diff type.
@item @kbd{C-<return> (Evil)} (@code{majutsu-diff-visit-workspace-file})
@kindex C-<return> (Evil)
@findex majutsu-diff-visit-workspace-file
Visit the workspace file without conflicting with Evil's @code{C-j} section navigation.
@item @kbd{- (Vanilla)} (@code{majutsu-diff-less-context})
@kindex - (Vanilla)
@findex majutsu-diff-less-context
Decrease the context for diff hunks by COUNT lines.
@item @kbd{= (Evil)} (@code{majutsu-diff-less-context})
@kindex = (Evil)
@findex majutsu-diff-less-context
Decrease the context for diff hunks by COUNT lines.
@item @kbd{+} (@code{majutsu-diff-more-context})
@kindex +
@findex majutsu-diff-more-context
Increase the context for diff hunks by COUNT lines.
@item @kbd{0 (Vanilla)} (@code{majutsu-diff-default-context})
@kindex 0 (Vanilla)
@findex majutsu-diff-default-context
Reset the context for diff hunks to the default height.
@item @kbd{~ (Evil)} (@code{majutsu-diff-default-context})
@kindex ~ (Evil)
@findex majutsu-diff-default-context
Reset the context for diff hunks to the default height.
@item @kbd{t (Vanilla)} (@code{majutsu-diff-toggle-refine-hunk})
@kindex t (Vanilla)
@findex majutsu-diff-toggle-refine-hunk
Toggle word-level refinement.
@item @kbd{T (Vanilla)} (@code{majutsu-diff-toggle-fontify-hunk})
@kindex T (Vanilla)
@findex majutsu-diff-toggle-fontify-hunk
Toggle syntax highlighting within diff hunks. With a prefix argument@comma{} cycle between highlighting the current hunk on selection and highlighting all hunks immediately.
@end table

When Evil mode is active@comma{} Majutsu follows evil-collection's
conventions for Magit diff buffers: @code{+} still increases context@comma{} @code{=}
decreases it@comma{} and @samp{~} resets it to the default.

When @samp{--color-words} is enabled@comma{} Majutsu renders the old/new line numbers in
the left margin and uses "@dots{}" lines to split hunks.
With refinement enabled@comma{} color-words hunks also show a shadow cursor on the
paired side (controlled by @samp{smerge-refine-shadow-cursor}).
With Vanilla bindings@comma{} file visits through @code{RET} or @code{C-j} still respect the
side at point by using stored line/column metadata from the color-words
backend.

With Evil bindings@comma{} @code{RET} visits the side at point and @code{C-<return>} forces the
workspace file; @code{C-j} remains section navigation.  File visits use the same
stored line/column metadata from the color-words backend.
@end enumerate

@node File and Blob Inspection
@subsection File and Blob Inspection

Majutsu's file inspector is implemented by @samp{majutsu-file} and can be used both
from command prompts and with defaults derived from the current section context.

Commands:
@deffn Command majutsu-find-file
Prompt for revset + path (defaulting from point when possible) and open that file as a blob.
@end deffn

@deffn Command majutsu-find-file-other-window
Like @code{majutsu-find-file}@comma{} but display the blob in another window.
@end deffn

@deffn Command majutsu-find-file-other-frame
Like @code{majutsu-find-file}@comma{} but display the blob in another frame.
@end deffn

Blob buffers are read-only snapshots with history-aware navigation:
@table @asis
@item @kbd{p / n} (@code{majutsu-blob-previous / majutsu-blob-next})
@kindex p / n
@findex majutsu-blob-previous / majutsu-blob-next
Jump to the previous or next revision that touched this file@comma{} while preserving cursor position as much as possible.
@item @kbd{V (Vanilla)} (@code{majutsu-blob-visit-file})
@kindex V (Vanilla)
@findex majutsu-blob-visit-file
Jump to the workspace version of the same file.
@item @kbd{C-c m} (@code{majutsu-blob-visit-magit})
@kindex C-c m
@findex majutsu-blob-visit-magit
Open the current blob in Magit's blob viewer.
@item @kbd{b} (@code{majutsu-annotate-addition})
@kindex b
@findex majutsu-annotate-addition
Start annotate for the current blob.
@item @kbd{g (Vanilla)} (@code{revert-buffer})
@kindex g (Vanilla)
@findex revert-buffer
Revert or reload the current blob content.
@item @kbd{g r (Evil)} (@code{revert-buffer})
@kindex g r (Evil)
@findex revert-buffer
Revert or reload the current blob content.
@item @kbd{e / C-x C-q} (@code{majutsu-blob-edit-start})
@kindex e / C-x C-q
@findex majutsu-blob-edit-start
Enter editable blob mode (wdired-style).
@end table

Blob navigation keys are disabled while editing@comma{} so blob-mode bindings do not
interfere with text edits.

@table @asis
@item @kbd{C-c C-c} (@code{majutsu-blob-edit-finish})
@kindex C-c C-c
@findex majutsu-blob-edit-finish
Apply changes through non-interactive @samp{jj diffedit} and exit edit mode. Majutsu copies current buffer text into the diffedit right side and finishes automatically@comma{} without opening the right-side temp file buffer.
@item @kbd{C-x C-q} (@code{majutsu-blob-edit-exit})
@kindex C-x C-q
@findex majutsu-blob-edit-exit
Leave editable mode. If modified@comma{} it prompts to save or abort; if unchanged@comma{} it exits immediately.
@item @kbd{C-c C-k} (@code{majutsu-blob-edit-abort})
@kindex C-c C-k
@findex majutsu-blob-edit-abort
Abort blob edits@comma{} restore the original content@comma{} and restore the original cursor position.
@end table

Evil normal-state behavior depends on whether the blob is read-only or
editable:

@table @asis
@item @kbd{i} (@code{majutsu-evil-blob-insert-dwim})
@kindex i
@findex majutsu-evil-blob-insert-dwim
Enter editable blob mode and stay in normal state.
@end table

@table @asis
@item @kbd{i} (@code{evil-insert-state})
@kindex i
@findex evil-insert-state
Enter insert state.
@end table

Editable mode also changes cursor visuals (see
@code{majutsu-blob-edit-cursor-type}); with Evil@comma{} the normal-state cursor is updated
too.

@node Annotate (Blame)
@subsection Annotate (Blame)

Majutsu annotate is implemented by @samp{majutsu-annotate} and uses
