@node Understanding Tags
@section Understanding Tags

In Jujutsu@comma{} tags are lightweight refs that point to revisions@comma{} similar to Git tags.
Majutsu wraps @samp{jj tag set/list/delete} and follows jj semantics where creating and
moving tags both use @samp{tag set} (moving requires @samp{--allow-move}).

@node Tag Transient
@section Tag Transient

Tag commands are intentionally dispatch-first.

@table @asis
@item @kbd{? t} (@code{majutsu-tag})
@kindex ? t
@findex majutsu-tag
Open the tag transient.
@end table

Transient actions:
@table @asis
@item @kbd{l} (@code{majutsu-tag-list})
@kindex l
@findex majutsu-tag-list
List tags in a dedicated buffer.
@item @kbd{s} (@code{majutsu-tag-set})
@kindex s
@findex majutsu-tag-set
Set tag(s). Uses completion and allows new names.
@item @kbd{m} (@code{majutsu-tag-move})
@kindex m
@findex majutsu-tag-move
Move existing tag(s) to another revision (internally @samp{--allow-move}).
@item @kbd{d} (@code{majutsu-tag-delete})
@kindex d
@findex majutsu-tag-delete
Delete tag(s) by name or pattern.
@end table

Tag prompts use completion candidates from local tags. Existing tags are shown for
selection@comma{} while set/delete prompts still allow entering string patterns manually.

